President Barack Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts. Meghan Flanz has been appointed as Assistant Secretary for Human Resources and Administration at the Department of Veterans Affairs. Carla A. Harris has been appointed as Chairperson of the National Women's Business Council. H. Fisk Johnson has been appointed as a member of the Advisory Committee for Trade Policy and Negotiations. Mark Tercek has also been appointed as a member of the Advisory Committee for Trade Policy and Negotiations. Joshua Bolten and Stuart Levey have been appointed as members of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. President Obama expressed confidence that these individuals will help tackle the important challenges facing America.